March 25 (Reuters) - Russia's National Settlement Depository (NSD) on Friday said Clearstream, one of the world's biggest settlement systems, had informed it that it was blocking its account and waiting for a decision from regulatory authorities in Luxembourg, Interfax reported. Clearstream and Euroclear are no longer accepting Russian assets, effectively shutting off an exit route for overseas investors.  read more  Our Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles.